                          Labor Market Information

   How to Reach the Labor Market Information Division
   The Labor Market Information Division of the Employment Development
   Department promotes California's economic health by providing
   information to help people understand California's economy and make
   informed labor market choices. In addition to employment and
   unemployment statistics, LMID provides economic planning information,
   industry and occupational information, social and demographic
   information, and a variety of other data.

   If you are interested in the other services available from the
   Employment Development Department, such as finding job openings or
   filing for unemployment insurance, please see our Index of Services and
   Programs. Job openings are available on the Internet at CalJOBS or see
   our Department Directory for the EDD office near you.

   There are several ways to contact Labor Market Information staff:

     Send an E-mail:

     * Send e-mail to the LMI Webmaster at lmid.webmaster@edd.ca.gov if
       you have questions on finding data online, or technical questions
       about the website.
     * Send a message about other programs within the Employment
       Development Department such as filing for Unemployment Insurance,
       help with CalJOBS, or employer tax rates.
     * If you have a question concerning labor law or employer/employee
       disputes, please contact the California Department of Industrial
       Relations at info@dir.ca.gov

     Local Labor Market Area Consultants:

   Located throughout California, local Labor Market Consultants help
       people find, access, and use labor market information products and
       services. They analyze local labor force and industry employment
       data along with other economic statistics, and provide custom
       research for agencies involved in workforce preparation and
       economic development.

     By Phone:

   EDD - Labor Market Information Division, Publications and Information
       Unit
       in Sacramento, California:

   Voice: (916) 262-2162
       FAX: (916) 262-2443

     By Mail or In Person:

   Employment Development Department
       Labor Market Information Division
       Attn: Publications and Information Unit
       7000 Franklin Blvd., Suite 1100
       Sacramento, CA   95823

